Name: 1,3,5,7-Tetraazatricyclo[3.3.1.13.7]decane; Hexamethylenetetramine
Rationale for classification: The substance is classified as flammable, and its powder or granules, when mixed with the air, may cause dust explosion according to ICSC (2004). Classified into Division 4.1 and Packing Group III (UN#1328) (UN Recommendations on the Transport of Dangerous Goods).

Name: Cresol
Classification: Not applicable (m-cresol)           Not classified (o- and p-cresol)
Rationale for classification: Classified as "liquid" (m-cresol), according to GHS criteria. Classified into Division 6.1 and Class 8 (UN Recommendations on the Transport of Dangerous Goods, UN#2076 and 3455) (o- and p-cresol).

Name: Carbon black
Classification: Not classified(Materials of animal or vegetable origin), Classification not possible(Materials of mineral origin)
Rationale for classification:
It is based on Animal-and-plant materials: the UN number 1361 (CARBON, animal or vegetable origin, Class4.2, Packing Group IIorIII).
Mineral materials: No data.

Name: Lead phosphite dibasic
Rationale for classification: UNRTDG is classified into 4.1, II, or III according to the UNRTDG No. (2989). In consideration of safety, it was classified as Category 1 adopting 4.1 and II.

Name: Sodium dodecan-1-yl sulfate
Rationale for classification:
Since it was classified into Class 4.1 and PG III in the United Nations Recommendations on the Transport of Dangerous Goods, it was classified into Category 2. 
In addition, this TDG classification is based on the UN number 1325 by Merck KGaA data from March 2009.

Name: chlorophenol
Classification:
Not applicable (o-) 
Classification not possible (m, p-)
Rationale for classification: Liquid (GHS definition) (o-)  No data available (m, p-)

Name: Polychlorinated terphenyls
Rationale for classification: PTCs had previously been used as fire-retardants (EHC 140 (1993)). Classified into Class 9 (UN#3151 (Polyhalogenated Biphenyls (liquid; excluding polychlorinated biphenyls (UN#2315, liquid); those with concentrations of not more than 50mg/kg are not included in the Dangerous Goods list), or Polyhalogenated Terphenyls (liquid; those with concentrations of not more than 50mg/kg are not included in the Dangerous Goods list)), UN#3152 (Polyhalogenated Biphenyls (solid; excluding polychlorinated biphenyls (UN#3432, solid); those with concentrations of not more than 50mg/kg are not included in the Dangerous Goods list), or Polyhalogenated Terphenyls (solid; those with concentrations of not more than 50mg/kg are not included in the Dangerous Goods list)) (UN Recommendation on the Transport of Dangerous Goods).
